<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Iran's Parliament Speaker Hashemi Rafsanjani, whose political position has 
strengthened since the Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini's death, was reelected to 
another one-year term, the official news agency IRNA said. It reported that 230 
out of 241 deputies at special session of the Iranian Parliament voted to 
retain the Speaker. Rafsanjani, 55, who is also the armed forces commander in 
chief, is the only declared candidate in the Aug. 18 presidential election. 
</P>
</TEXT>
