<HEADLINE>
<P>
ADMONITION TO OFFICEHOLDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Just an observation on Archbishop Mahony's policy statement on abortion. As a 
lawyer of some 55 years of active practice, I wish to congratulate him on his 
excellent argument against abortion and its application to Catholic and public 
officials. No attorney could have better presented the facts. It surely gives 
thought to all of them, whether elected or appointed. The easiest position for 
any of them to take is to straddle the fence by arguing that I am not 
pro-abortion, but I will leave it to my constituents for their individual 
freedom of choice. 
</P>
<P>
It is great to be elected to office, but after obtaining the positions, none of 
them can cast aside the fact that abortion is murder and human sacrifice. 
</P>
<P>
Unfortunately, abortion will, undoubtedly, be with us, but it should not be 
legalized and funded with taxpayers' dollars. I am tired of hearing about 
everyone's rights, but seldom a word of their obligations. 
</P>
<P>
FREDERICK C. DOCKWEILER 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
