<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: COUNTYWIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The new 1989-90 San Diego County Grand Jury was chosen Monday in a drawing at 
the County Courthouse downtown and will be sworn in June 30. 
</P>
<P>
County Clerk Robert D. Zumwalt drew the 19 names from a box that contained an 
initial pool of 62 people. Eleven alternates were also selected. Those in the 
drawing were nominated by judges in the Municipal and Superior courts. 
</P>
<P>
The new Grand Jury will serve from July 1 through June 30, 1990. The jury is 
empowered to examine issues within city and county government. It has the 
authority to investigate special districts, joint-powers agencies and nonprofit 
corporations. 
</P>
<P>
The jury also handles citizen complaints and, under certain circumstances, may 
hold hearings in criminal investigations to determine whether enough evidence 
has been presented by the district attorney to warrant a trial. 
</P>
<P>
The new members are: 
</P>
<P>
George J. Bruns, 64, San Diego, retired contractor; Payton C. Cook, 67, San 
Diego, retired school principal; Ramon Cordizin, 66, Bonita, retired Realtor; 
Edward Crute, 74, San Diego, retired Boys' Club administrator; R. H. Dorman, 
67, Coronado, retired Navy commander; William Emerton, 65, San Diego, retired 
purchasing official; John Phil, 72, Oceanside, retired general manager; James 
R. Fury, 72, San Diego, retired U.S. Marine Corps, and David M. F. Goldberg, 
63, San Diego, retired company president. 
</P>
<P>
Also Joan G. Lightner, 38, San Diego, homemaker; Betty Long, 54, El Cajon, 
homemaker; Ruth Mailin, 53, La Jolla, retired social worker; Marcia L. Malkus, 
51, La Mesa, retired teacher; Marguerite M. Peele, 64, Coronado, retired 
physician; Raymond Stedly, 71, La Mesa, retired labor union employee; Richard 
G. Turnbull, 72, Oceanside, retired small-business owner; Mildred W. Watson, 
64, Chula Vista, retired controller; George T. Wise, 50, San Diego, 
businessman, and Steven R. Zorich, 65, San Diego, retired school administrator. 
</P>
