<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN KILLS HIMSELF ON POLICE STATION'S STEPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Reseda man, despondent over losing his job, walked nearly a mile from his 
home to a Los Angeles police station Monday and fatally shot himself on the 
building's front steps, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Front desk officers at the West Valley Division station in the 19000 block of 
Vanowen Avenue heard the shot and saw the man drop to the pavement outside the 
glass front doors about 2 a.m., police said. 
</P>
<P>
The officers ducked to safety, thinking that someone was shooting at the 
station, but later determined that Alan Matta, 21, had shot himself with a 
rifle. He was taken to Northridge Hospital Medical Center, where he died about 
an hour later, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The incident was under investigation, but police said it appeared that the man 
became despondent and left the house he shared with his mother and stepfather. 
</P>
</TEXT>
