<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: SIERRACIN CORP. TO SELL INTREX TO COURTAULDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sierracin Corp., a Sylmar aerospace company, said it has reached a final 
agreement to sell its Intrex operation for $5.5 million to Courtaulds United 
States Inc. Intrex makes coatings used in aerospace and military parts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
