<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PLAN FOR DISNEY HOTEL ADVANCES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Disney Development Co. won approval Monday to start planning for the 
construction of a 800- to 1,200-room hotel on a site across the bay from the 
Queen Mary in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
The Long Beach Redevelopment Agency Board voted to give Disney Development, the 
real estate arm of the Walt Disney Co., exclusive negotiation rights for the 
oceanview site near Shoreline Drive and Pine Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Disney is deciding whether to develop a resort hotel in conjunction with the 
building of a major theme park at the Queen Mary. 
