BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Movie Tickets Shoot to $7.50: A major movie theater chain said it will charge 
$7.50 a ticket on weekends in its Manhattan theaters, a new national high for 
film admissions. Cineplex Odeon, the Toronto-based chain that owns six theater 
complexes in New York and New Jersey, said the $7.50 admission price will be in 
effect Friday nights and all day Saturday and Sunday. The price represents an 
increase of 50 cents a ticket, or 7.14% -- less than the 8.3% increase in the 
consumer price index for the same period in New York, according to a Cineplex 
statement. Film admissions in most American cities range from $5 to $7. 
</P>
