<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BREA; 
</P>
<P>
2 KILLED ON FREEWAY AS CAR GOES OUT OF CONTROL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Santa Ana men were killed when their car hit the concrete center divider of 
the Orange Freeway, slid through four lanes of southbound traffic, spun out of 
control, then came to a stop when it struck a tree, a California Highway Patrol 
spokesman said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
CHP spokesman Matt Clark identified the men killed shortly after 9 p.m. Sunday 
as Ricardo Guzman, 21, and Jose Luis Cruz, 20, who was driving the Chevrolet 
Monte Carlo. 
</P>
<P>
They were pronounced dead at the scene, Clark said, adding that it appeared 
that both were under the influence of alcohol. 
</P>
<P>
Two passengers in the car were treated at Brea Community Hospital for minor 
injuries, Clark said. 
</P>
<P>
Clark said a witness told the CHP that the men were following his car too 
closely just north of Birch Street when Cruz abruptly changed lanes, then hit 
the center divider. 
</P>
<P>
Cruz's car did not strike any other vehicles as it bounced back through the 
four lanes of traffic and eventually hit the tree. 
</P>
</TEXT>
