<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALMANAC / ORANGE COUNTY CROP REPORT: NURSERY STOCK, FLOWERS TOP LIST OF CROP 
VALUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For the 20th straight year, nursery stock and cut flowers topped the list of 
Orange County crops ranked by dollar value, according to the 1988 Orange County 
Crop Report. 
</P>
<P>
Nursery stock was valued at $123.9 million, a decline of 2% from 1987 but 
almost triple the value of the second-place crop, strawberries, and about six 
times the value of third-place Valencia oranges. 
</P>
<P>
Gross dollar value as measured in the report includes cost of production, 
harvesting and preparation for market, and does not reflect net return to the 
producer. 
</P>
<P>
Increases in the animal industry, orchard and truck crops helped push the gross 
value of all crops to $253.6 million, a 3% increase over 1987's total. 
</P>
<P>
