<P>
HOW AGRICULTURAL MIX HAS CHANGED 
</P>
<P>
The value of Orange County's nursery, orchard and vegetable crops have 
increased substantially since 1968, while the animal industry's dollar value 
has declined. The gross value of all Orange County agricultural products has 
more than tripled since 1968 to $253.6 million. Chart at left does not include 
value of apiculture and field crops. Charts at right show how use of county 
farm acreage has changed since 1968. 
</P>
